description: Creates a signing profile. A signing profile is a code-signing template that can be used to carry out a pre-defined signing job.

parameters.name: profileName
parameters.description: The name of the signing profile to be created.

parameters.name: signingMaterial
parameters.description: The AWS Certificate Manager certificate that will be used to sign code with the new signing profile. The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the certificates that is used to sign your code.

nested_params.name: certificateArn
nested_params.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the certificates that is used to sign your code.

parameters.name: signatureValidityPeriod
parameters.description: The default validity period override for any signature generated using this signing profile. If unspecified, the default is 135 months. value (integer) --- The numerical value of the time unit for signature validity. type (string) --- The time unit for signature validity.

nested_params.name: value
nested_params.description: The numerical value of the time unit for signature validity.

nested_params.name: type
nested_params.description: The time unit for signature validity.

parameters.name: platformId
parameters.description: The ID of the signing platform to be created.

parameters.name: overrides
parameters.description: A subfield of platform. This specifies any different configuration options that you want to apply to the chosen platform (such as a different hash-algorithm or signing-algorithm). signingConfiguration (dict) --- A signing configuration that overrides the default encryption or hash algorithm of a signing job. encryptionAlgorithm (string) --- A specified override of the default encryption algorithm that is used in a code-signing job. hashAlgorithm (string) --- A specified override of the default hash algorithm that is used in a code-signing job. signingImageFormat (string) --- A signed image is a JSON object. When overriding the default signing platform configuration, a customer can select either of two signing formats, JSONEmbedded or JSONDetached. (A third format value, JSON, is reserved for future use.) With JSONEmbedded, the signing image has the payload embedded in it. With JSONDetached, the payload is not be embedded in the signing image.

nested_params.name: signingConfiguration
nested_params.description: A signing configuration that overrides the default encryption or hash algorithm of a signing job.

nested_params.name: encryptionAlgorithm
nested_params.description: A specified override of the default encryption algorithm that is used in a code-signing job.

nested_params.name: hashAlgorithm
nested_params.description: A specified override of the default hash algorithm that is used in a code-signing job.

nested_params.name: signingImageFormat
nested_params.description: A signed image is a JSON object. When overriding the default signing platform configuration, a customer can select either of two signing formats, JSONEmbedded or JSONDetached. (A third format value, JSON, is reserved for future use.) With JSONEmbedded, the signing image has the payload embedded in it. With JSONDetached, the payload is not be embedded in the signing image.

parameters.name: signingParameters
parameters.description: Map of key-value pairs for signing. These can include any information that you want to use during signing. (string) --- (string) ---

parameters.name: tags
parameters.description: Tags to be associated with the signing profile that is being created. (string) --- (string) ---

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the signing profile created.

nested_items.name: profileVersion
nested_items.description: The version of the signing profile being created.

nested_items.name: profileVersionArn
nested_items.description: The signing profile ARN, including the profile version.
